The 18-inch model of King Kong was made from a metal mesh skeleton, a mixture of rubber and foam for the muscle structure and rabbit fur for his hair.

The 18-minute documentary ventures up the garden paths and down the Euphrates Creek, exploring how this 100-year-old wood made it into our lives today. It's the story of a place that shouldn't exist in Kansas and the people who have loved it. Every aspect of the film was made in Kansas by Kansans. It was underwritten with a grant from the Kansas Humanities Council as part of their initiative 'Kansans Tell Their Stories' for the state's 150th anniversary.

"Las Lloronas" is an adaptation of the legend of "La Llorona"(Weeping Woman). It's based on the story of three generations of women within a Mexican familiy. Cursed by la llorona, these women fight to overcome the situations that arise by this. Through the struggles that these women face, they must eventually come to terms with destiny. "Las Lloronas" is a story of love, loss and triumph of the spirit, as well as the inner strength that each women has within.
